snippet.textDisplay: This hit me hard. Today is Friday February 14th, 2020. Today is the day we laid my 95 year old Great Grandma  Lucille to rest. Today we said our final goodbyes. No one wants to say goodbye ever. Whether it’s 26 years old or 95 years old, no one is ready. The way Xavier talked about his brother saving his life broke me down. I have two older brothers, I am the youngest out of three. The way Xavier described his brother to you is pure love. I broke down hearing that story imagining as if I was in his shoes and my brother was calling me. There is no bond tighter than a bond between brothers and family. With that being said, don’t skip out on spending time with family and loved ones. You don’t know how much time you have left with them. Our lives can change in a split second. Make sure to live your life to the fullest and take nothing for granted.    May Xavier’s love and legacy live on and may his soul Rest In Peace.     Thank you for sharing this video.

snippet.textDisplay: I totally understand the pain of all of this. During my freshman year, I lost a really close friend due to cancer. Then in the summer, I heard my mom and aunt have cancer both stage four (mom has ovarian and my aunt had lung). During the summer of 2019, I lost my aunt. In December I lost my grandfather(everyone loses their grandparents, but my situation is different. I'm adopted you see, and all the males in my family were just awful so obviously, I wasn't allowed to talk to them, except my grandfather. He was the only good male in my genetics. I have and still have to much to learn from him.) and hurt me. Then just in January, I found out that my mom is supposed to die next year so I am making the best of what I have left. So yeah it hurts. But if anyone is reading this and is going through the same thing PLEASE PLEASE PLEASE go talk to somebody. I do not care if you are emotionally, mentally, or physically hurt. Or none at all. I would so give my life up to see or hear or feel any of them again. You have to go talk to somebody. And if you are like me you have so many tests you have to study for, trying to figure out college and your future, you are just trying to survive high school. So again talk to somebody, ANYONE! A teacher, friend, or maybe a parent. Just go talk.

snippet.textDisplay: This video really hit home hard, I lost my fiancé Kate on the 30th July 2019 the day before her 26th birthday we where together for 7 years and 29 days 😥💔 she lost her life to a heart condition she never knew she had, a 3rd degree atrioventricular block, also known as a heart block where the signals from the brain to the heart telling it to best become cut of, that day started like no other day we both had that Tuesday of as Kate was a nurse and worked most weekend and I work in retail management and also work most weekends, we woke up that morning at around 10am and went downstairs I had a cup of coffee and Kate had an apple for breakfast we where sat out in our garden and I went back upstairs and went on the Xbox for a bit waiting for Kate to come back up and start getting ready, about an hour went by so I went back downstairs to see what she was doing and she was lead on the sofa and said she wasn’t feeling well, so I left her there to rest and went back upstairs on the Xbox for an hour then cane back down to check out her again it was about 12pm by now and she’s gotten a lot worse and said her heart felt weird like that she could feel it struggling 😥 so we called an ambulance And she got progressively worse we had to recall an ambulance 3 times they took over 2 hours to get here! They turned up around 2:30pm shortly after my last call pleading them to come because Kate was in a seriously bad way she couldn’t even sit herself up by then 😥 the ambulance eventually turned up about 2:30pm and took her to hospital I didn’t go with her so I could call her family members and explain what was happening and I went and picked her mother up from her work place at about 3pm and we went to the hospital Kate had been taken to... we where taken into a private side room straight away and told Kate had been taken into intensive care and was put on life support but they didn’t actually know by that tone what was causing it... more hourse went by and at 8:30pm the drs came back to talk to us in the room we where in and explained Kate had gone into cardiac arrest but they managed to get her back and where working on a plan and thought they’re figured out what was going on but she would have to be taken to London for immediate surgery to save her and started talking through the options with me and her mother... 😥 but the dr we where talking to got pages that Kate had gone into a second cardiac arrest they had a whole team working on her but a 9pm the dr who had been consulting us throughout the day came back out to us and explained that she wasn’t going to make it and now was our tone to say goodbye 💔😥 i stayed by her side until the very end I had to leave when they said they where going to have to give up that she was gone :( she died at 9:15pm that day 💔 the post mortem confirmed the atrioventricular block the drs had suspected as the cause of death leading to complete heart failure 😪  I miss her so much anything can happen to anybody at any time never take life or loved ones for granted!
